    "Both groups of physicians preferred specialist answers over model answers.",
    "Specialists preferred model answers over generalist answers, while generalists rated them about equally.",
    "Table 2 | Med-PaLM 2 performance on multiple-choice questions with and without overlap Dataset Overlap fraction Performance (without overlap) Performance (with overlap) Delta MedQA (USMLE) 12/1,273 (0.9%) 85.3 [83.4, 87.3] 91.7 [76.0, 100.0] -6.3 [-13.5, 20.8] PubMedQA 6/500 (1.2%) 74.1 [70.2, 78.0] 66.7 [28.9, 100.0] 7.4 [-16.6, 44.3] MedMCQA 893/4,183 (21.4%) 70.5 [68.9, 72.0] 75.0 [72.2, 77.9] -4.6 [-7.7, -1.3] MMLU Clinical Knowledge 55/265 (20.8%) 88.6 [84.3, 92.9] 87.3 [78.5, 96.1] 1.3 [-6.8, 13.2] MMLU Medical Genetics 48/100 (48.0%) 92.3 [85.1, 99.6] 91.7 [83.8, 99.5] 0.6 [-11.0, 12.8] MMLU Anatomy 37/135 (27.4%) 82.7 [75.2, 90.1] 89.2 [79.2, 99.2] -6.5 [-17.4, 8.7] MMLU Professional Medicine 79/272 (29.0%) 89.1 [84.7, 93.5] 92.4 [86.6, 98.2] -3.3 [-9.9, 5.5] MMLU College Biology 60/144 (41.7%) 95.2 [90.7, 99.8] 96.7 [92.1, 100.0] -1.4 [-8.7, 7.1] MMLU College Medicine 47/173 (27.2%) 78.6 [71.4, 85.7] 91.5 [83.5, 99.5] -12.9 [-22.4, 0.1]",
